        <trans-unit id="130" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Tooltips are displayed when the pointer rests on a property name.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="131" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The <bpt id="p1">[</bpt>CMFCPropertyGridToolTipCtrl<ept id="p1">](../../mfc/reference/cmfcpropertygridtooltipctrl-class.md)</ept> class displays a tooltip so that it is easily readable by the user.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="132" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Usually, the position of a tooltip is determined by the position of the pointer.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="133" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>By using this class, the tooltip appears over the property name and resembles the natural property extension, so that the property name is fully visible.</source>
        </trans-unit>
